    "summary": "Illustrates the process for handling a modem returned by a customer, detailing its re-entry into the inventory system, subsequent testing, and repackaging.",
    "whatItShows": "This flowchart details the re-entry process for a modem that has been returned by a customer after its initial packaging and shipment. It covers the stages from customer return and registration, through system detection of re-entry, incrementing the modem's cycle, creating a new cycle record, and finally, the re-testing and potential repair or repackaging.",
    "whenToUse": "Use this diagram to visualize inventory management processes for returned items, especially electronics or devices that undergo multiple lifecycle stages. It's suitable for illustrating workflows involving re-entry, testing, and re-packaging of products.",
